// copilot.proto — Connect-RPC contract for the `copilot` bounded context.
//
// Powers the Druz9 Copilot desktop client: a stealth AI assistant that runs
// on the user's macOS, captures screenshots via a global hotkey, and streams
// LLM responses into a floating window invisible to screen-share viewers.
//
// Screenshots are NEVER persisted — they flow client → backend → LLM and are
// discarded once the completion returns. A boolean flag on the message row
// records that the turn included an image. See docs/copilot-architecture.md.
//
// Analyze and Chat are server-streaming RPCs (token deltas → final Done).
// Vanguard does not transcode streaming RPCs to REST — desktop clients must
// use the native Connect path for real-time streaming. REST fallbacks return
// only the final JSON body.

